frameDefinitions: A Resource is depleted by some process, resulting in there being only a Remainder in existence some time into or after the process.
A Protagonist is in the dynamic, maintained state of being alive or has exited this state.
An entity is integrated into a vehicle as a Part of a (possibly unexpressed)
The words in this frame describe a period of time, as opposed to a point in time.
A Guest stays for a time at a Location, which is not his or her permanent residence, for some Duration.

An Experiencer actualizes a certain pattern of behavior, a Lifestyle, which persists for a significant period of time in the Experiencer's life and is recognized as part of his character or normal routine.
frameExamples: There are only two poems <t>left</t> from Quayle
The car's <t>engine</t> started smoking so we pulled over.
The best <t>time</t> of year for planting tends to be fairly regular.
I usually <t>stay</t> with my aunt at her summer house when I go to Seville.
He <t>lived</t> a hedonistic life before he settled down.
listRoleDefinitions: The part of the Resource that the Process has not yet applied to.
The original set of items to which the Depletive_process applies one after the other.
The individual who owned the Resource that is being depleted.

A temporal setting or event which metonymically stands for the entities that were in existence then. The <fen>Remainder</fen> is part of the <fen>Original_context</fen>. This role occurs especially when abstract entities such as social institutions are seen as <fen>Resource</fen>s.
The Time when the amount of the Resource that is let is assessed.
<fen>Protagonist</fen> identifies the being or entity that is  dead or alive.
This role identifies the <fen>Figure</fen> or form being described by the target.
The time in which the <fen>Protagonist</fen> is dead or alive.
Some <fex name='Part'>Part</fex> of the larger vehicle, the <fex name='Whole'>Whole</fex>.
A vehicle (the <fex name='Whole'>Whole</fex>)  which includes the <fex name='Part'>Part</fex>.
A quantity or other characterization of the <fen>State</fen>'s duration.  In this frame, the duration can be inexact.
An ongoing state whose duration can be measured.
The <fen>Guest</fen> remains for a relatively short period of time in the <fen>Location</fen>.
The <fen>Location</fen> where the <fen>Guest</fen> spends a short amount of time.
The length of time that the <fen>Guest</fen> remains at the <fen>Location</fen>.
The <fen>Host</fen> is living at the <fen>Location</fen> on a permanent basis, and is allowing the <fen>Guest</fen> to stay there.
The time at which the temporary stay takes place.
The <fen>Place</fen> indicates the larger physical setting of the temporary stay.
The person who actualizes a pattern of behavior.
A pattern of behavior which the actions of the <fen>Experiencer</fen> matches for a significant period of time.
The <fen>Lifestyle</fen> may be characterized by a <fen>Manner</fen>, which is often expressed adverbially.
A temporal description of when the <fen>Experiencer</fen> adopts a <fen>Lifestyle</fen>.
The spatial location where the <fen>Experiencer</fen> carries out a <fen>Lifestyle</fen>.
